.me\/p95VHY-3UW","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":14882,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/10\/eat-blessed-suhur\/","url_meta":{"origin":15062,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Suhur: Blessings in pre-fasting morning meal","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 10, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cTake the pre-fasting meal, for surely there are blessings in the pre-fasting meal.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1923, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1095 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0633\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":4035,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/03\/fasting-haram-eid-fitr-adha-tashriq\/","url_meta":{"origin":15062,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Eid: The Prophet forbids fasting on the two Eids","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 3, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu 'Ubayd reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cO people, the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, has prohibited you from fasting on the days of these two celebrations, Eid al-Fitr and Eid al-Adha. One of them is the day you break\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33152,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/08\/10\/mustahab-iftar-for-pilgrims\/","url_meta":{"origin":15062,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Hajj: Pilgrims not fasting on the day of Arafat","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 10, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Maymunah reported: People had doubts about the fasting of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, on the day of Arafat. She sent him a cup of milk while he was standing on the plain and he drank from it while the people were looking at him. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3721,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/07\/18\/zakat-al-fitr-ramadan\/","url_meta":{"origin":15062,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Ramadan: Zakat al-Fitr at end of Ramadan","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 18, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, obligated payment of charity at the end of Ramadan, a portion of dates or barley, upon slave and freeman, male and female, young and old among the Muslims. The Prophet ordered it to be given before people\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":27566,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/04\/15\/permission-not-fast-journey\/","url_meta":{"origin":15062,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Travel: Permission to fast or not on journey, whatever is easiest","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 15, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: Hamzah ibn Amr asked the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, about fasting while traveling. The Prophet said, \u201cIf you wish, you may fast. And if you wish, you may break your fast.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1841, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1121 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15069,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/07\/15\/sunset-time-break-fast\/","url_meta":{"origin":15062,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Fasting: When sun sets, time for Iftar","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 15, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Umar ibn al-Khattab reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen the night approaches from the east and day retreats from the west and the sun has set, it is time to break the fast.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1954, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1100 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/15062","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[